19 January:

    Build Landing Page:
                        1) Databases: Local and Online Mongo and Mysql.
                        2) Setup ngBootstrap.
                        3) Install Angular and Cordova

Steps:

    1) npm init --yes (Generate package.json within server folder)
    2) npm install express body-parser cors mongoose bcryptjs jsonwebtoken passport passport-jwt  --save
    3) npm install --save-dev babel-cli babel-preset-env
    4) touch .babelrc in backend folder  add to file { "presets": ["env"] }
    5) add to package.json scripts : "dev": "babel-watch server.js"
    6) create server.js file. routes/api
    7) Install MongoDB: install dependencies manually via terminal then installar.exe
    7.2) sudo service mongod start, sudo service mongod stop,
    8) app.use(express.static(path.join(__dirname,'public'))) create public folder for angular build.
    9) Install lamp sudo apt install lamp-server^
    10) install php7.1, install phpmyadmin , sudo service apache2 restart
    11) sudo cp /etc/phpmyadmin/apache.conf /etc/apache2/conf-available/phpmyadmin.conf
    12)  Add mysql auth:  ALTER USER 'root'@'localhost' IDENTIFIED WITH mysql_native_password BY 'ur pwd';
    13) sudo ng add @ng-bootstrap/schematics (Post installation Angular Cordova)
    14) install Gradle
    15) sudo cordova build ; sudo cordova run browser ; sudo cordova platform add android ; sudo cordova run android/ --emulator ;

